	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">The Balrog is Dead,  Long Live The Balrog!</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(4.12)</font> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=22702">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9813">Andrew "Bee Boy" Sitte</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9813&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Your crew of Dwarves kill The Balrog to reclaim Moria, while your own Balrog wreaks massive havoc.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> April 9, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Starting<br>
  Frodo, Reluctant Adventurer<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(182)">The One Ring, The Ruling Ring</a><br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(35)">Gimli, Son of Gloin</a><br>
  Gloin, Friend to Thorin<br>
<br>
Adventure Deck<br>
  [1] Hobbiton Woods<br>
  [2] <a href="javascript:card_browser(214)">Trollshaw Forest</a><br>
  [3] <a href="javascript:card_browser(217)">Council Courtyard</a><br>
  [4] <a href="javascript:card_browser(224)">Mithril Mine</a><br>
  [5] <a href="javascript:card_browser(228)">The Bridge of Khazad-dum</a><br>
  [6] Lothlorien Woods<br>
  [7] <a href="javascript:card_browser(233)">Anduin Wilderland</a><br>
  [8] <a href="javascript:card_browser(238)">Shores of Nen Hithoel</a><br>
  [9] <a href="javascript:card_browser(242)">Summit of Amon Hen</a><br>
<br>
The Balrog is Dead (32):<br>
  Fror x2<br>
  Farin x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(194)">Sting</a> x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(309)">Dwarven Axe</a> x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(55)">Gimli&#39;s Helm</a> <br>
  Hand Axe x4 <br>
  Dwarven Bracers x3 <br>
  Gimli’s Battle Axe x2 <br>
  Endurance of Dwarves x2 <br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(139)">Stairs of Khazad-dum</a> x3 <br>
  Flurry of Blows x4 <br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(190)">Power According to His Stature</a><br>
  Till Durin Wakes Again x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(114)">Lord of Moria</a> x2 <br>
<br>
Long Live the Balrog (34):<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(72)">Goblin Runner</a> x4<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(73)">Goblin Scavengers</a> x4<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(75)">Goblin Scimitar</a> x4<br>
  Goblin <a href="javascript:card_browser(303)">Armor</a>y x4<br>
  Final Cry x4<br>
  Fill With <a href="javascript:card_browser(314)">Fear</a><br>
  Whip of Many Thongs x3<br>
  The Balrog&#39;s Sword x3<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(843)">The Balrog, Durin&#39;s Bane</a> x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(91)">They Are Coming</a> x3<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(82)">Host of Thousands</a> x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This deck was designed for two of the greatest joys of Lord of the Rings: Killing their Balrog, and wreaking havoc with your Balrog.  After site 5, both halves of the deck are pretty much screwed (though the Free Peoples still can make it).  Play this deck for fun once or twice (and remember when you&#39;re rating the deck that it&#39;s a FUN deck) but make sure your opponent actually uses The Balrog first ;-)<br>
<br>
The Balrog is Dead!<br>
The Free Peoples side is made up of the stuff that&#39;s gonna kill The Balrog, as well as general helper stuff so you can actually get to site 9 afterwards.  Get Gimli set up with his axe, bracers, and a Hand Axe, and get at least one Lord of Moria into play.  With this setup, all it takes is one Flurry of Blows and 2 exertions to make Gimli 18 strength, Damage +4, enough to kill The Balrog.  With enough help, Gloin can even do it (though it takes 2 Flurrys and 2 Lord of Morias).  As a bonus, Dwarves blow through your deck, helping you draw the cards that make your own Balrog unstoppable.<br>
<br>
Long Live The Balrog!<br>
Everything on you shadow side is designed to fly through your deck to get everything you need in hand by site 5, and to ensure you the shadow to do it when your opponent gets there.  Your opponent will likely double move to site 3, but only single-move to 5.  That seems like a good idea against Moria, but their double-move to 5 would help them since you&#39;re using common Balrog anyway.  <br>
<br>
Lets say that they move to The Bridge using No Strangers so that you only get 7 twilight.  With 2 Armories in play, that&#39;s enough to play The Balrog, Whip, Sword, and 3 Final Cry.  If you can pull that off, you&#39;ll be pretty much guaranteed to kill 2 companions.  Gandalf cancels with his Staff?  2 Final Crys.  Sam Stealths?  2 Final Crys.  Filibert Bolger?  1 Final Cry.  Boromir with Armor?  Whip, dead.  Aragorn with Armor?  Whip, Final Cry, dead.  Of course, if Bororare is unarmed, The Balrog will have the 21 strength needed to overwhelm him (and Aragorn too if &#39;gorn is less than 11 strength).<br>
<br>
Fill With Fear lets you get rid of Aragorn&#39;s and Elven bows.  Runners, Scavengers, Scimitars, and Armories are just there to burn through your deck.  As a bonus, with a nice draw you can add enough twilight at site 4 to play The Balrog from your hand if you have him.  Your opponent will stop rather than have The Balrog follow them to 5, and move to 5 thinking that you&#39;ve used your only Balrog and they&#39;re safe.<br>
<br>
You COULD go with Flame of Udun, but then I&#39;d recommend playing 3 Fill with Fears to ensure there&#39;s no Archery phase.  That plus his +2 twilight cost is the reason I went with Durin&#39;s Bane.  Getting him out at site 4 AND 5 is loads of fun, and it&#39;s very hard to get Flame out at 4.<br>
<br>
Site stuff:<br>
Hobbiton Woods: Avoid Weathertop, Weatherhills, and Bree Streets<br>
Trollshaw Forest: Lots of possessions means lots of cards to draw!<br>
Council Courtyard: Cuz it&#39;s good.<br>
Mithril Mine: Play Scimitars, add Twilight, draw cards, play an early Balrog.<br>
The Bridge: This is where the fun happens!<br>
Lothlorien Woods: Heal Frodo; Not Dimrill Dale cuz your orcs suck anyway.<br>
Anduin Wilderland: Archery-B-gone<br>
Shores of Nen Hithoel:  Who knows, you might actually get 5 orcs out if you&#39;re lucky<br>
Summit of Amon Hen: So you can draw the 3 Whips buried at the bottom of your deck and curse your luck. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=22702"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=22702" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
